                <h1>Will Expunged Records Affect Your Background Check?</h1>
                <p>If your record is expunged, it typically means that it is removed from public view, and you should pass a standard background check. Employers often check databases that include convictions, so an expungement can assist in portraying you in a positive light. However, some checks may still reveal certain details depending on jurisdiction.</p>
